					</p>
		<div class="comment-content">
			<p>I assume (and this could be a mistake, so advance apologies) that companies had to self-nominate for an award, as is normally the case with these things.  If this is the case perhaps the recycling of the talent pool is down to the way in which the nomination process is marketed?</p>
<p>In terms of this being &#8220;a shocking indictment of the cityâ€™s creative scene&#8221;: how much of a worry is this?  Is anybody looking at these awards other than ourselves?  Is this an award ceremony that says anything to the wider creative industries, outside of the B postcode area?</p>
